# mattpocock skill symlinks under skills/ are never committed. They no longer
# belong here (mattpocock is NOT build-distributed anymore — Claude uses the
# native plugin, Codex/Cursor install via `install.py manual` into
# ~/.agents/skills/). build runs _clean_mattpocock_skill_symlinks to remove
# any stale ones; these ignore rules guard against accidentally recreating
# and committing them (which breaks Cursor marketplace clones: broken
# ../vendor links Cursor's safety scan rejects as "unsafe source path").
